        h1 About Me

        p Tony Shorrocks is an insturmental teacher, performer, coach, and mentor with a very wide knowledge and experience of music education gained over a 40 year career as as musician and teacher.

        br

        h2 Performance

        p Over his career he has gained playing experience with the BBC Northern Symphony Orchestra/BBC Philharmonic, Royal Liverpool Philharmonic, City of Birmingham Symphony Orchestra, Opera North, and others in the North of England.

        p He has also performed baroque chamber music on period instruments with Sprezzatura, the English Baryton Trio, Sonnatas a tre and on modern instruments in Italy as principal viola of the Adriatica Sinfonica and more recently with Ensemble Quartetto Montefiore piano quartet.

        p Outside of classical music his career is still very varied, as a performer he has worked on pop music tours with Elaine Page, Shirley Bassey, Howard Keele, Johnny Dangworth, George Shearing, the Beverley Sisters, Kid Creole and the Cocoanuts, Top of the Pops with Dusty Springfield and others.

        br

        h2 Conducting / Directing

        p For 20 years he directed and conducted the Liverpool University Symphony Orchestra, taking them on tours to Italy, Germany and France and the Chamber Orchestra to its own 10 day summer course in Normandy. He gained his teaching experience at the College of Ripon and York St. John, then Liverpool Hope University and since 1995 at Liverpool University, and on being appointed as Head of Performance a year later (1996) set out to develop a performance course for the undergraduate degree that annually attracted positive comment from the external examiners reports. Building on that success a masters level course was developed with a symbiotic performance and pedagogy content.

        p Currently Tony is Artistic Director of the international youth orchestra project “Music, a Bridge Between People” with orchestral members drawn from 12 Meditereanean countries and has just been appointed to a consultant to a large Beijing music teaching school.
